locality: Yemen, gov. Al-Mahra, wadi immidiately N. of Shahrut, running W. to E. between 16º 34' 07,0 N, 52º 46' 32,5 E and 16º 34' 10,5 N, 52º 46' 38,4 E.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Hawf Mts, Uteq, S facing slopes with big boulders, below the vertical rock face of the summit escarpment. Rocky gorge with steep slopes, scattered trees and shrubs. Alt.: 1000-1100 m. 29.9.2001, Leg.: P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. Reisch YP 496.

Oman: Dhofar, Jabal Qamar, 1 km S of junction of the track to Shaat with Salalah-Sarfayt road, 16°47'N, 53°36'E, 930 m, escarpment into a gorge; dense scrub. Alt.: 930 m. 6.10.1998, Leg.: N. Kilian & P. Hein NK 5483.

Yemen: Al-Mahra. coastal mountains, N of Hawf, slopes ENE of the village Con. Anogeissus-Acacia woodland (Acacia dominated). Alt.: 700-860 m. 14.11.2000, Leg.: N. Kilian, S. O. Bahah, P. Hein, M. A. Hubaishan & C. Naumann NK 6833.

Oman: Oman, Dhofar: Jabal Qara, monsoon affected rocky ridge near the track between Raysut and Qaftawt, Euphorbia balsamifera zone, cushion plants dominant, alt. 750 m, 17°03'N, 53°54'E. Shrub, 1 m tall. Alt.: 750 m. 3.10.1998, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 5228b.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. coastal mountains between Al Faydami and Hawf, 2.plateau and slopes around the village Con. Anogeissus-woodland (4-6(-8) m tall) and parkland with Maytenus- and Dodonaea-shrubs (2-3 m tall)Small trees 2-4 m tall. [BGBM-Akz-Nr.: 314-07-00-10]. Alt.: 650-800 m. 14.11.2000, Leg.: P. Hein & N.
